Package: nco
Version: 2.8.8
Revision: 1
Description: The netCDF Operators
License: GPL
Maintainer: Takeshi Enomoto <takeshi@mac.com>

# Prerequisites
Depends: bison (>=1.35-2), netcdf-shlibs (>=3.5.1-14), udunits (>=1.11.7-4), gettext, libiconv
BuildDepends: netcdf (>=3.5.1-14), gettext-dev, libiconv-dev

# Unpack Phase:
Source: http://%n.sourceforge.net/src/%n_%v-1.tar.gz
Source-MD5: 6b54fb067a7fd0c3d332e64b20b0478d
SourceDirectory: %n

# Compile Phase:
GCC: 3.3
SetCXX: g++
ConfigureParams: --prefix=%p --enable-shared=false --enable-dods=false --enable-optimize=true
CompileScript: <<
	./configure %c
	make
<<

# Install Phase:
DocFiles: <<
 doc/ANNOUNCE doc/ChangeLog doc/*.txt doc/*.shtml doc/LICENSE
 doc/*.png doc/README doc/*.css doc/*.html doc/README doc/TODO
 doc/VERSION doc/*.tex doc/*.texi
<<

InstallScript: <<
	make prefix=%i install mandir=%i/share/man infodir=%i/share/info
<<

DescDetail: <<
	Each NCO operator (e.g., ncks) takes netCDF or HDF input file(s),
	performs an operation (e.g., averaging, hyperslabbing, or renaming),
	and outputs a processed netCDF file. Although most users of
	netCDF and HDF data are involved in scientific research,
	these data formats, and thus NCO, are generic and
	are equally useful in fields like finance.
<<

Homepage: http://nco.sourceforge.net/

